---
alwaysApply: true
---

- You are an expert in TypeScript, Node.js, Next.js App Router, React, Shadcn UI, Tailwind, Framer Motion, React Hook Form, Zod, and Zustand.

- Code Style and Structure
  - Write concise, technical TypeScript code with accurate examples.
  - Use functional and declarative programming patterns; avoid classes.
  - **Single Component per File:** Each file MUST contain only ONE primary component.
  - **File Structure:** Exported component -> Sub-components (if small/internal) -> Helpers -> Static content -> Interfaces/Types.
  - Use descriptive variable names with auxiliary verbs (e.g., `isLoading`, `hasError`, `isAuthorized`).

- Naming Conventions & File Organization
  - **File Naming:** Use **camelCase** for all files (e.g., `userProfile.tsx`, `authWizard.tsx`).
  - **Directory Naming:** Use lowercase with dashes (e.g., `src/components/auth-forms`).
  - **Shared Components:** `src/components` is reserved ONLY for truly reusable UI atoms (buttons, inputs, shared layouts).
  - **Private Components:** Components used within a specific page MUST be placed in a `_components` folder inside that page's directory (e.g., `src/app/dashboard/_components/`).
  - Favor named exports for all components.

- TypeScript & State Management
  - **Global State:** Use **Zustand** for global state management. Stores must be located in `src/stores/` and follow a clean separation of actions and state.
  - **Types:** Prefer **interfaces** over types. Avoid enums; use **literal types** or **maps**.

- Forms & Validation
  - **Standard:** Use **React Hook Form** integrated with **Zod** for all form handling and validation.
  - **Schema Location:** Define Zod schemas and default values at the end of the file (static content section) to keep the render function clean.
  - Use `z.infer<typeof schema>` for form types.

- UI and Styling (Hard Rules)
  - **Zero Border Radius:** Strictly use `rounded-none` for all elements (cards, buttons, inputs, modals). NO rounded corners allowed.
  - **Modern Startup Aesthetics:** Minimalist, high-trust, high-contrast.
  - **Typography:** Prioritize "Geist" or "Inter". Headings must be bold and clean.
  - **Borders:** Ultra-thin and muted (e.g., `border-slate-200/50` or `border-black/[0.05]`).
  - Use Shadcn UI (modified to `rounded-none`) and Tailwind CSS.

- Performance & Key Conventions
  - **RSC First:** Prioritize Server Components. Use `'use client'` sparingly and only at the leaf nodes.
  - **URL State:** Use `nuqs` for managing state via URL search parameters.
  - **Optimization:** Wrap client components in `Suspense` with a fallback; use dynamic loading for heavy components.
  - **Images:** Use WebP format, include explicit size data, and use `https://placekitten.com/` for placeholders.

- API Communication & Service Layer (Mandatory)
  - **Service-Based Architecture:** Every Backend interaction must go through a dedicated service object in `src/services/`.
  - **Domain Folder Structure:** Organize services by domain using `src/services/<domain>/` (e.g. `src/services/auth/authService.ts`, `src/services/auth/authTypes.ts`).
  - **No Direct Fetch:** Direct use of `fetch`, `axios`, or `apiRequest` inside Components or Stores is prohibited.
  - **Standard Client:** Use the `apiRequest` wrapper from `@/lib/api/http.client`.
  - **Type Integrity:**
    - Every service file (e.g. `userService.ts`) must live beside its corresponding type file (e.g. `userTypes.ts`) inside the same domain folder.
    - Use **Interfaces** for API Responses and **Literal Types** for Payloads.
    - All methods must explicitly return `Promise<T>`.
    - Keep API-specific contracts inside the service domain folder. Only move broadly shared app types to `src/lib/<domain>/types.ts` or `src/types/`.
  - **Example Structure:**
    ```typescript
    // src/services/chat/chatService.ts
    export const chatService = {
      async sendMessage(body: SendMessageBody): Promise<MessageResponse> {
        return apiRequest<MessageResponse>("/api/v1/chat", {
          method: "POST",
          body,
        });
      },
    };
    ```

- Project Structure
  - Root: All application code must be under the `/src` directory.
  - `/src/app`: Application logic, routing, and page-specific `_components`.
  - `/src/components`: Shared UI atoms and global layouts.
  - `/src/stores`: Zustand store definitions.
